[% IF program.kayakalpa %]
<h2>Kaya Kalpa Wellness Center</h2>
Kaya Kalpa means rejuvenation of body and spirit and our professionally
trained practitioners are dedicated to your well-being. We offer a variety
of Ayurveda therapies, traditional massage and other body therapies to
enhance your stay at Mount Madonna Center. Nestled among majestic oak
and redwood trees, on 355 acres overlooking Monterey Bay, Kaya Kalpa
Wellness Center offers an oasis for relaxation, health and nurturing. 
<ul>
<li>We encourage you to schedule your appointment as far in advance as
  possible to ensure a practitioner is available for your particular request.
<li>Phone and email messages are checked daily.
<li>A scheduler will be present during Friday evening dinner and Saturday
  morning brunch in the lobby of the Community Building.
<li>Please arrive 10 minutes before your appointment.
<li>Inquire about contraindications when scheduling your appointment.
</ul>
To schedule bodywork:
<p class=p2>
<table cellpadding=3>
<tr><td align=right>Office Phone</td><td>408-847-3276</td></tr>
<tr><td align=right>Cell Phone</td><td>408-483-6326</td></tr>
<tr><td align=right>e-mail</td><td><a href="mailto:kayakalpa@mountmadonna.org">kayakalpa@mountmadonna.org</a></td></tr>
</table>
<p class=p2>
For more information see our web site:
<a href="http://www.mountmadonna.org/projects/kayakalpa">www.mountmadonna.org/projects/kayakalpa</a>
<p class=p2>
We look forward to your visit!
<p class=p2>
Services are subject to practitioner availability.
<h3>Ayurveda Services</h3>
Ayurveda is the traditional Indian science of health and comes
from the Sanskrit words, Ayur meaning life and veda meaning knowledge.
We are pleased to offer these ancient healing techniques for
bringing harmony, peace and balance to one's mind, body and spirit.
<p class=p2>
<h4>Swedana</h4>
An oiling of the entire body using long, slow rhythmic techniques,
followed by a rosemary and eucalyptus steam in our cedar steam cabinet.
The treatment is completed with a body dusting, using organic barley
flour and a dry brushing which exfoliates and refreshes the skin.
Swedana helps the process of detoxification by inducing sweat,
calming the mind and alleviating muscle and joint pain. 
Ask us about contraindications.<br>
$125 (75 min)
<h4>Shirodhara</h4>
A warm ginger pack is placed on the back while you enjoy a head, neck,
shoulder, hand and foot massage. This is followed by a steady stream
of warm organic oil over the forehead. Deeply relaxing, soothing and
rejuvenating, this treatment calms the nervous system and helps
relieve stress, headaches, insomnia and exhaustion.<br>
$110 (60 min) or add-on to another treatment for $70 (30 min)
<h4>Abhyanga</h4>
A vigorous, warm oil massage, stimulating the lymphatic system.
Deeply nourishing, Abhyanga style massage relaxes muscles and moves
prana (life force energy).<br>
$110 (60 min)
<h4>Marma Point Face Massage Add-On</h4>
Warm organic almond oil massaged over the vital facial points.
A soothing addition to most treatments.<br>
Add-on to any treatment for only $35 (30 min)
<h3>Bodywork</h3>
<h4>Swedish Massage</h4>
Light to firm massage using warmed oils.<br>
$85 (60 min), $125 (90 min)
<h4>Stone Massage</h4>
With warm, organic oil and warmed stones. The heat from the stones
penetrates into the muscles for revitalization and groundedness.
Ask about contraindications before scheduling.<br>
$110 (60 min), $125 (70 min)
<h4>Reiki</h4>
A gentle hands-on approach to balance and harmonize one's subtle energies.
Reiki is restorative and nurturing, calms emotional distress and relaxes 
an over stressed body. It can be enjoyed alone or as a complement to 
other services. Recipient is fully clothed.<br>
$75 (60 min), $100 (75 min)
<h3>Extras to add on ...</h3>
<h4>Aromatherapy</h4>
Aromatherapy can enhance your oil massage experience. We offer 
eight aromatherapy oils at no additional charge, hand made from our 
own 'Ayurveda World.' Please let your practitioner know if you would 
like any of these aromatic scents added to your massage oil:
geranium, jasmine, lavender, lotus, rose, sandalwood, tulsi and wintergreen.
<h4>Herbal Steam</h4>
Enhance the detoxification and cleansing process after a massage or
abhyanga with the exquisite experience of an herbal steam with fresh
organic herbs in our cedar steam cabinet. Ask about contraindications.<br>
$25 (up to 11 minutes)
<h4>Marma Point Face Massage</h4>
Warm organic almond oil is massaged over the facial vital points 
using an Ayurveda technique. Marma Point Massage can be enjoyed 
after most treatments.<br>
$35 (30 minutes)
<h4>Therapeutic Oil</h4>
Crafted on site by a resident herbalist using organic sesame oil
and local herbs, these therapeutic oils enhance your experience.
Choices include: rosemary (soothing, eases tired and overworked muscles),
arnica (an anti-inflammatory to relieve bruising, strains, sprains 
and muscle soreness) or rose geranium (strengthens muscles).<br>
$5
<h4>Shirodhara</h4>
A steady stream of organic oil over the third eye.
An excellent addition to a massage or Abhyanga.<br>
$70 (30 min)
